<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC 97906 - Delco-Remy 22SI Alternator Resistor Cable</stitle>
    <afc id="AFC97906">
        <afcnum>97906</afcnum>
        <afcdate>March, 1998</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subject>Delco-Remy 22SI Alternator Resistor Cable</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Delco-Remy</vendor>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This AFC applies to all models without 3+1 battery systems and built before August 1, 1997 with
                    Delco-Remy 22SI alternators.
                </para>
                <para>Some battery chargers impose electrical pulses on the battery terminal of the alternator that can
                    feed through the bridge diode capacitance and turn the auto-start module on. In this static
                    condition, without the benefit of cooling from the alternator fan, the auto-start module may fail
                    internally. The failure mode may result in the alternator drawing current while the ignition key is
                    in the off position resulting in discharged batteries. This condition exists on Delco-Remy 22SI
                    alternators built prior to July 1, 1997 or date coded earlier than 97G01 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790601">Figure 1</hotlnk>). The addition of a resistor cable assembly from the "R"
                    alternator terminal to ground will eliminate this problem.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9790601" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9790601" filename="../afcfigures/g9790601.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
