        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9790602">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9790602" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g9790602" filename="../afcfigures/g9790602.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>The alternator "BAT" terminal is live. If a tool is shorted at the alternator "BAT" terminal
                        the tool can heat up enough to cause a skin burn.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the push on terminal end of the resistor cable assembly to the "R" terminal on
                    the alternator rear cover.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The "R" terminal may have a rubber protective cover installed which must be removed and
                            discarded.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the eyelet end of the resistor cable assembly to the boss on the alternator rear
                    cover with the self tapping 8-32 screw provided in Kit 10457646. Tighten the screw to 20 to 46
                    in-lbs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the resistor cable assembly to existing vehicle wiring with a tie strap or
                    electrical tape.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
